SIMPLE: middlings
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Middlings
<hw>Mid"dlings</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
combination of the coarser parts of ground wheat the finest bran,
separated from the fine flour and coarse bran in bolting; -- formerly
regarded as valuable only for feed; but now, after separation of the
bran, used for making the best quality of flour. <xex>Middlings</xex>
contain a large proportion of gluten.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In the southern and western parts of the United
States, the portion of the hog between the ham and the shoulder; bacon;
-- called also <altname>middles</altname>.</def>
<rj><au>Bartlett.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Middy</ent>⟦br⟧
